Source: webcleaner
Section: web
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Bastian Kleineidam <calvin@debian.org>
Standards-Version: 3.6.1
Build-Depends: python2.3-dev, debhelper (>= 4.1.16), debconf (>= 1.2.9), dpatch, gettext

Package: webcleaner
Architecture: any
Depends: python2.3, debconf (>= 1.2.9), python2.3-imaging
Suggests: webcleanertools
Description: a filtering HTTP proxy
 Features:
 * HTTP/1.1 support
 * integrated HTML parser, removes unwanted HTML (adverts, flash, etc.)
 * integrated JavaScript engine, allows popup filtering
 * compress documents on-the-fly (with gzip)
 * disable animated GIFs
 * filter images by size, removes certain banner adverts
 * reduce images to low-bandwidth JPEGs
 * remove/add/modify arbitrary HTTP headers
 * usage of SquidGuard domain and url blacklists
 * Basic and Digest proxy authentication for both clients and servers
 * per-host access control
 * completely customizable over web interface

Package: webcleanertools
Section: x11
Architecture: all
Depends: fxpy-python2.3 (>= 1.0.0), python2.3, webcleaner
Description: configuration and visualization tools for webcleaner
 additional tools and helper applications for webcleaner:
 .
 webcleanerconf is a nice GUI configuration tool for the WebCleaner proxy.
 .
 wcheaders is a graphical interface to display the HTTP headers
 of all requests the local WebCleaner proxy handles.

